We had such a good experience here. The food was delicious and the service was great. Our waitress was patient explaining the menu to us and the chef stopped by once to how everything was. For 9,70€ we got a big plate of bacon/mozzarella ravioli, a beef empanada, bread, a brownie, a glass of wine and a bottle of water. It's down an alley that feels a little sketchy but well worth it. Clean, comfy and friendly.
